The paper discusses the use of GANs for image synthesis, semantic image editing, style transfer, image superresolution, and classification, which are all topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of GANs for learning deep representations without extensively annotated training data, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the competitive process involving a pair of networks, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SD.
